The Herald Nyore Madzianike Senior Court Reporter Norton legislator, Temba Peter Mliswa, accused of violating the Covid-19 national lockdown regulations after calling a Press conference at his Borrowdale residence in Harare has been freed on $20 000 and has been barred from convening any other press conferences pending his trial. Mliswa, who was being represented by lawyer Mr Musindo Hungwe, was also ordered to report once a week at Borrowdale Police Station. He appeared before Harare provincial magistrate Mrs Vongai Guwuriro. Mr Charles Muchemwa and Mrs Constance Ngombengombe appeared for the State.